The different forms of government are so many forms of subordination, so many relations of superior and inferior, that is, so, many relations of uncquals. Public law, then, is a law of Status, and the law of Persons or law of Status in the private code is the intrusion of a portion of the public code into the private code3 or, in barbarous and semi-civilized legisla- tions, the disfigurement of private law by the introduction of relations that properly belong to public law.
